# Swagger/OpenAPI Documentation Rules

## Setup

- Use @nestjs/swagger for API documentation
- Configure Swagger in `main.ts`
- Swagger available at `/api/docs`

## Decorators

Add decorators for API documentation:
- `@ApiTags('Requests')` - Group endpoints
- `@ApiOperation({ summary: 'Get all requests' })` - Endpoint description
- `@ApiResponse({ status: 200, description: 'Success' })` - Response documentation
- `@ApiBearerAuth()` - For protected endpoints
- `@ApiBody({ type: CreateRequestDto })` - Request body documentation
- `@ApiParam({ name: 'id', type: 'number' })` - Path parameter documentation
- `@ApiQuery({ name: 'page', required: false })` - Query parameter documentation

## Example

```typescript
@Controller('api/requests')
@ApiTags('Requests')
@ApiBearerAuth()
export class RequestsController {
  @Get()
  @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Get all requests' })
  @ApiResponse({ status: 200, description: 'List of requests' })
  @ApiQuery({ name: 'page', required: false, type: Number })
  async findAll(@Query() query: GetRequestsDto) {
    return this.requestsService.findAll(query);
  }

  @Post()
  @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Create request' })
  @ApiResponse({ status: 201, description: 'Request created' })
  @ApiResponse({ status: 400, description: 'Bad request' })
  @ApiBody({ type: CreateRequestDto })
  async create(@Body() dto: CreateRequestDto) {
    return this.requestsService.create(dto);
  }
}
```

## DTO Documentation

Add decorators to DTO properties:
```typescript
export class CreateRequestDto {
  @ApiProperty({ description: 'Request title', example: 'Need website design' })
  @IsString()
  @IsNotEmpty()
  title: string;
}
```
